<p><strong>Education</strong></p>

<p>I read for a <strong>second</strong> BA in <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/2017/feb/23/ppe-oxford-university-degree-that-rules-britain?CMP=fb_gu">Philosophy, Politics and Economics</a> with senior status at the University of Oxford. I was supported by the KC Mahindra Scholarship, Tiara Special Grant, and a second undergraduate degree scholarship by Harris Manchester College.</p>

<p>At Oxford, I  wrote an <a href="../files/research/ppethesis.pdf">thesis on congestion option pricing</a>  and specialized in philosophy of maths. <a href="/philosophy">These are some essays</a> from that time.</p>

<p>Before Oxford, I graduated from IIT Delhi with a five-year Integrated Masters in Maths and Computing in 2013. My masterâ€™s thesis in the <a href="../files/research/thesis.pdf">design of approximation algorithms for networks</a> under <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Naveen_Garg">Naveen Garg</a> (awarded an outstanding grade).</p>

